    {
      id: "0200000000FC0000",
      title: "Old Habits Die Hard",
      x: 21,
      y: 4,
      tasks: [
        {
          id: "0300000000FC0000",
          type: "item",
          item: "ae2:storage_bus"
        }
      ],
      description: ["  There may be some cases where you would prefer to use another storage method outside of the ME system, such as Storage Drawers.  For those cases there is the &lStorage Bus&r.  Attach this onto the inventory system where both input and output operations can occur (such as on a Drawer Controller)."],
      icon: "ae2:storage_bus",
      dependencies: ["02000000000E0000"],
      rewards: [
        {
          id: "0400000000FC0000",
          type: "random",
          table_id: 360287970189705216
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      id: "0200000000FD0000",
      title: "Annihilate! Formulate?",
      x: 10,
      y: 2,
      tasks: [
        {
          id: "0300000000FD0000",
          type: "item",
          item: "ae2:annihilation_plane"
        },
        {
          id: "0300000000FD0001",
          type: "item",
          item: "ae2:formation_plane"
        }
      ],
      description: ["  The &lAnnihilation Plane&r will instantly mine any block that is in front of it and import its broken products into the ME system.  This might be useful for vanilla cobble generators and similar constructions.", "", "  The &lFormation Plane&r will instantly place configured blocks or items in the space in front it, whenever an Annihalation Plane was activated.  You also have the option of dropping blocks as items instead of placing them in the world.", "", "  The pair might be useful for some uncommon or rare block drops, such as flint from gravel.  In such a setup you'd place a Formation plane two blocks above an Annihilation Plane and have the gravel blocks fall down into the Annihlation Plane.", "", "&4&l&oWarning:&r This can easily become a lag machine if you are not careful!", "", "  The &lIdentity Annihilation Plane&r will instantly mine a block as if it had the silk touch enchantment."],
      icon: "ae2:formation_plane",
      dependencies: ["0200000001530000"],
      rewards: [
        {
          id: "0400000000FD0000",
          type: "random",
          table_id: 360287970189705216
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      id: "0200000000FE0000",
      title: "Better Than Wifi!",
      x: 13,
      y: 5,
      tasks: [
        {
          id: "0300000000FE0000",
          type: "item",
          item: "ae2:wireless_terminal"
        },
        {
          id: "0300000000FE0001",
          type: "item",
          item: "ae2:wireless_crafting_terminal"
        }
      ],
      description: [" &l Wireless Terminals&r and &lWireless Crafting Terminals &rallow you to access your ME system without needing to stand by an ME Terminal that's anchored down to a cable somewhere.", "", "  In order to do this, however, they need to be within range of a &lWireless Access Point&r, which start off with about an 16 block range.  This range can be improved up to 512m from the access point by installing &lWireless Boosters&r, this comes at the cost of more power, however.", "", "  They also need to be linked to the ME System, and the only way to do this is through the &lSecurity Terminal&r.", "", "  Lastly, they consume energy for the entire duration you have its GUI open. It doesn't consume energy per request, however."],
      icon: "ae2:wireless_terminal",
      dependencies: ["0200000001550000"],
